      <body>
         <head>
            <p>To <persName>
                        <ptr target="../persons/pers2198">James West</ptr>
                    </persName>
                    <note place="foot" n="1">
                        <p>Although the <nationality>English</nationality> part of the
                           <event>
                                <seg ana="SevenYearsWar FrenchInvasion">Seven Years' <seg ana="war">War</seg>
                                </seg> (<date from="1756" to="1763">1756–63</date>)</event> began only with its declaration of <seg ana="war">war</seg> on <date when="1756-05-15">May 15, 1756</date>, tensions with
                           <placeName>
                                <country>France</country>
                            </placeName> had been brewing
                     throughout <date when="1755">1755</date>. Rumors of an <seg ana="FrenchInvasion">invasion</seg> were rife. By the beginning of <date notBefore="1755-12-01" notAfter="1755-12-07">December</date> (perhaps <date notAfter="1755-12-01">earlier</date>), <persName>
                                <ptr target="../persons/pers0001">JW</ptr>
                            </persName> had begun to
                     'discipline' some
                           <personGrp>
                                <placeName>
                                    <region>London</region>
                                </placeName>
                        <personGrp>Methodists</personGrp>
                            </personGrp><!--Again, I&apos;m trying to tag *both* "London Methodists" and "Methodists" as groups. Perhaps there is a way to sub-set "London" within "Methodists"?-->
                     'for <seg ana="military">soldiers</seg>, and they'd begun exercising
                     at the <placeName>Foundery</placeName>' (<bibl>
                                <persName>Thomas
                           Illingworth</persName> diary, <date when="1755-12-14">Dec. 14,
                           1755</date>, at <placeName>
                                    <institution>Duke
                           University</institution>
                                </placeName>
                            </bibl>). <persName>
                                <ptr target="../persons/pers2177">Charles Wesley</ptr>
                            </persName> wrote to
                           <persName>
                                <ptr target="../persons/pers2191">his wife</ptr>
                            </persName> on
                        <date when="1755-12-07">Dec. 7, 1755</date>: '<persName>
                                <ptr target="../persons/pers0001">My brother</ptr>
                            </persName> tells me the
                        <name nationality="French">French</name><!--How do we identify PEOPLE based on their PLACES?--> are
                     expected every hour by <persName>
                                <ptr target="http://viaf.org/viaf/30157581760333782588">General
                        Hawley</ptr>
                            </persName><!--Lt. Gen. Henry Hawley.-->, in battle array, etc.;
                     that the <orgName>
                                <seg ana="government">Government</seg>
                            </orgName><!--Would this be correct, or should it be <orgName government="BritishGovernment">?-->
                     have not the least doubt of the <seg ana="war FrenchInvasion">invasion</seg>,
                     but will do their best to repel force by force.' <persName>
                                <ptr target="../persons/pers2177">He</ptr>
                            </persName> continued, 'I
                     question whether <persName>
                                <ptr target="../persons/pers0001">my
                        brother</ptr>
                            </persName>'s <seg ana="military">soldiers</seg>, with all
                     his pains and haste to train them up, will not be too tardy to rescue us.'
                     About <date when="1756-01-31">Jan. 31, 1756</date>
                     <persName>
                                <ptr target="../persons/pers2177">he</ptr>
                            </persName><!--Charles Wesley--> wrote that he planned to return to
                           <placeName>
                                <settlement>Bristol</settlement>
                            </placeName>
                     <date when="1756-02-07">a week later</date>—‘unless <person nationality="French" role="soldier military">Jack
                     Frenchman</person><!--This doesn&apos;t seem to be a proper name; instead, I think it&apos;s "an unspecific French soldier." But how might we explain that?!-->
                     snaps me up'. On <date when="1755-12-20">Dec. 20</date> the <orgName>
                                <seg ana="government">Privy
                     Counsel</seg>
                            </orgName><!--Most likely this is a group (legal) of advisors (to the king). I wasn&apos;t sure if it constituted an <orgName> or <personGrp> tag. At any rate, it is clearly "government-related"!-->
                     issued a royal proclamation<!--Can we link to the proclamation itself?-->
                     appointing <date when="1756-02-06">Friday, Feb. 6</date>, as a national Fast
                     Day when prayers should be offered for <persName>God</persName>'s help in
                     'the present situation of public affairs'.</p>
                  <p>This letter contains <persName>
                                <ptr target="../persons/pers0001">JW</ptr>
                            </persName>'s official offer of
                        <personGrp>Methodist</personGrp>
                     <seg ana="military">military support to the government</seg>, via
                           <persName>
                                <ptr target="../persons/pers2198">James West</ptr>
                            </persName>
                     (c. <date from="1704" to="1772-01-01">1704-72</date>), a Member of <seg ana="government">
                                <orgName>Parliament</orgName>
                            </seg> for
                           <placeName>
                                <settlement>St. Albans</settlement>
                            </placeName> who had been
                     at <placeName>
                                <institution>Balliol College, Oxford</institution>
                            </placeName> at
                     roughly the same time as <persName>
                                <ptr target="../persons/pers0001">JW</ptr>
                            </persName> was at <placeName>
                                <institution>Christ
                           Church</institution>
                            </placeName> and then
                           <placeName>
                                <institution>Lincoln</institution>
                            </placeName><!--All three of these are colleges within Oxford University.-->,
                     and who at <date when="1756-03">the time of this letter</date> was serving as
                        <occupation>Joint Secretary to <seg ana="government">the
                        Treasury</seg>
                            </occupation><!--This was James West&apos;s <occupation>, but does West himself need to be specified here? Also, this is another "government" tag——specifically, a government title.-->.
                     See <bibl>
                                <hi rend="italic">ODNB</hi>
                            </bibl>.</p>
                    </note>
                </p>
         </head>
         <opener>
            <placeName>
               <district>Marlborough</district>
            </placeName>
            <lb/>
            <date when="1756-03-01">March 1, 1756</date>
            <lb/>
            <lb/>
            <salute>Sir,</salute>
         </opener>
         <p>A few days since <persName>
                    <ptr target="../persons/pers2221">Mr. [George]
                  Whitefield</ptr>
                </persName><!--I can't insert the bracket symbol for the identifier. Is it needed?-->
            and I desired <persName>
                    <ptr target="../persons/pers0179">a friend</ptr>
                </persName> to
            ask your advice to whom it would be proper to make an offer of raising <seg ana="military">a company of volunteers</seg> for <seg ana="monarchy">
                    <persName>
                        <ptr target="../persons/pers0788"> his Majesty</ptr>
                    </persName>
                </seg>'s
            service. We apprehended the number would be about five hundred. Finding <persName>
                    <ptr target="../persons/pers2221">Mr. Whitefield</ptr>
                </persName> has since been
            persuaded that such an offer is premature, I am constrained to make the following
            independently on him.<note place="foot" n="2">It is possible that <persName>
                        <ptr target="../persons/pers2177">Charles Wesley</ptr>
                    </persName>'s scepticism
               infected <persName>George Whitefield</persName>, with whom <persName>
                        <ptr target="../persons/pers2177">CW</ptr>
                    </persName> informed <persName>
                        <ptr target="../persons/pers2191">his wife</ptr>
                    </persName> on <date when="1755-12-22">Dec. 22, 1755</date> that he had 'talked
               largely'.</note>
            </p>
         <p>To raise, for <seg ana="monarchy">
                    <persName>
                        <ptr target="../persons/pers0788">his
                     Majesty</ptr>
                    </persName>
                </seg>'s service, at least two hundred volunteers
            to be supported by contributions among themselves, and to be ready in case of an <seg ana="FrenchInvasion">invasion</seg> to act <date from="1756-03" to="1757-03">for a
               year</date> (if needed so long) at <seg ana="monarchy">
                    <persName>
                        <ptr target="../persons/pers0788">his Majesty</ptr>
                    </persName>
                </seg>'s
            pleasure, only within ___<note place="foot" n="3">A blank was left in the ms., obviously
               subject to discussion.</note> miles of
            <placeName>
                    <region>London</region>
                </placeName>.</p>
         <pb n="16"/>
         <p>If this be acceptable to <seg ana="monarchy">
                    <persName>
                        <ptr target="../persons/pers0788">his Majesty</ptr>
                    </persName>
                </seg>, they beg to have <seg ana="military">arms</seg><!--Should this ALSO have a "weapons" tag?--> out of <placeName theTower="theTowerOfLondon">the Tower</placeName>, giving the usual <seg ana="money">security</seg><!--Would "security" mean "monetary deposit"?--> for their return, and
            some of <seg ana="monarchy">
                    <persName>
                        <ptr target="../persons/pers0788">his
                     Majesty</ptr>
                    </persName>
                </seg>'s <seg ana="military">sergeants</seg> to
            instruct them in the <seg ana="military">military exercise</seg>.</p>
         <closer>I am now hastening to <placeName>
                    <settlement>Bristol</settlement>
                </placeName> on
            account of the election,<note place="foot" n="4">
                    <index indexName="works">See
                        <persName>
                            <ptr target="../persons/pers0001">JW</ptr>
                        </persName>'s <term cRef="27:16-17">letter to <persName>
                                <ptr target="../persons/pers0179">Blackwell</ptr>
                            </persName> of <date when="1756-03-04">Mar. 4,
                        1756</date>
                        </term>.</index>
                </note> concerning which I wrote to
                  <persName>
                    <ptr target="../persons/pers2177">my brother</ptr>
                </persName><!--I'm *FAIRLY* certain this would be CW, but I don't *ACTUALLY* know. There is no extant letter to CW from that time. Also, JW frequently uses the term "[my] brother" for people who are NOT his sibling(s).-->
            <date when="1756-02-21">last week</date>. But if my return to
                  <placeName>
                    <region>London</region>
                </placeName> would be of any service, you may
            command, sir, <signed>Your obedient servant,<lb/>
               <persName>John Wesley</persName>
            </signed>
         </closer>
      </body>
      <p>
            <hi rend="italic">Address</hi>: none; because hand delivered to <persName>
                <ptr target="../persons/pers2198">West</ptr>
            </persName> by <persName>
                <ptr target="../persons/pers0179">Ebenezer Blackwell</ptr>
            </persName> (whose transcription
         noted previously included the address, 'To The Honourable<!--Add <roleName>?-->
         <persName>
                <ptr target="../persons/pers2198">James West</ptr>
            </persName>, Esq.').</p>
